On March 9, 2018, the President signed three laws related to veterans. The first law, H.R. 1725, requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to report on the progress of an initiative aimed at improving the processing of certain veterans' claims for disability benefits. The second law, H.R. 3122, known as the "Veterans Care Financial Protection Act of 2017," mandates the VA to publish a warning on its website about financial and legal practices that could affect a veteran's eligibility for benefits. Lastly, H.R. 4533 designates the health care system of the Department of Veterans Affairs in Lexington, Kentucky, as the Lexington VA Health Care System and makes other specific designations.